          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Israel has approved a plan to escalate the offensive in Gaza, including the occupation of the Gaza Strip and continued control over captured areas. Credits: AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           PM Benjamin Netanyahu said the security cabinet had decided on a "<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-6-may-25-spotlight-h1-1-forceful-operation?source=website" target="_blank">forceful operation</a>" to destroy Hamas. The aim is to "conquer" the territory and sustain a presence. Israeli forces will advance deeper into Gaza, pushing civilians south while strengthening control over key areas. The plan aims to limit UN-led aid and replace it with Israeli-run hubs.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
         Netanyahu continues to promote Donald Trump’s proposal of the ethnic cleansing of Gaza. Humanitarian organizations have condemned the restrictions on aid distribution hubs, and Hamas has described the move as “political blackmail.” The Israeli government faces pressure from far-right coalition partners to reoccupy Gaza, but a significant faction of Israeli society is jaded by the war and actively protesting this. </p>
          
        </mj-text>
